      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Improve doctor runtime and schema drift diagnostics",
        "body": "Closes #85.\n\nAdds read-only `doctor --json` diagnostics for the active executable/runtime identity and local DB schema state, including supported/current versions, pending/newer migration flags, PR-detail storage support, and concise drift next steps.\n\nKeeps schema inspection diagnostic-only so `doctor --json` can report missing, newer, or legacy stores without applying migrations.\n\nDoctor JSON contract:\n- Scripts should inspect `db_schema.state` and `source_db_schema.state` for schema health.\n- Known schema drift still emits JSON diagnostics, including `runtime_open_error` for newer stores, so automation can report why the active binary cannot open the DB.\n- Non-schema runtime-open failures such as corrupt, locked, or unreadable DBs still emit `runtime_open_error` and return a nonzero runtime failure exit, preserving the existing script-facing failure signal.\n\nThe PR includes regression coverage for current, missing, newer, legacy/pending, and corrupt runtime-open states, plus no-mutation checks for diagnostic schema inspection.\n",
